Linux Architecture consist of inner most Hardware layer, kernel, shell, and outer application layer. Each layer has different functionalities and different uses. 

Linux follows a layered architecture:
	1. Hardware – CPU, RAM, devices ,All the hardware components such as motherboard, CPU, hard disk, etc. are comes under this layer
	
	2. Kernel – Kernel is the program which actually communicates with the hardware. Combining shell and kernel forms Operating System. Core of Linux, manages hardware and resources
	
	3. Shell – [Command interpreter (bash)]
	 Shell provides environment to run any application. It provides interface to the user to interact with hardware. We can say that it converts higher level language to lower level language. 
	
	4. System Libraries – Provide functions to applications
	
	5. Applications – User programs, Users interact with the system through varies applications such as office, games,etc.
	These applications run in outer layer of architecture. 
	
	 The kernel is the heart of Linux and controls everything
Operating Systems are the backbone of all computing devices. Linux stands out for its security, flexibility, and open-source nature, making it widely used in servers and modern technology.

